                "name": "Curt Weinstein",
                "href": "/profile/Curt-Weinstein"
            },
            "answer_text": "When the quotes ends first, before; when the quote includes the question mark, after. (OK, I am not so sure.) Are you the one who said, \u201cGive me liberty, or give me death\u201d? I like the complete phrase quoted before the question mark. He\u2019s the one who said, \u201cAm I my brother\u2019s keeper?\u201d In this case, the phrase includes the question mark; therefore I include the question mark in the quotes. OK, I am not sure these days of correct usage. But I like my method. (Don\u2019t use for school without checking modern usage; do use for stories.) ",
