                "name": "Stephanie Fysh",
                "href": "/profile/Stephanie-Fysh"
            },
            "answer_text": "It depends. The question mark goes inside the quotation mark when the question is part of the quotation: Then he asked me, \"Will you be at the party tonight?\" The question mark goes outside the quotation mark when it is the sentence containing the quotation that is a question: So what should I do if he says, \"See you there\"? (FYI, periods are always inside the quotation marks in North American English punctuation. It's not a universal rule.) ",
