                "href": "/profile/Alison-Parker-13"
            },
            "answer_text": "I have yet to see any advice on what should happen if the sentence is itself a question and the quotation ending it uses an interrobang. I\u2019d guess that the sentence would go like this: Did he really tell you, \u201cYou call this a life?!\u201d? [or . . .\u201cYou call this a life!?\u201d?]]. If you use an interrobang glyph, you\u2019d definitely end the sentence with a question mark unless you\u2019re as excited as the person quoted. Hey! Why not two interrobangs? This is uncharted territory, and here be monsters. ",
